>It's a good day for whole-fat milk.  Allison Aubrey's segment on the full
>fat paradox aired this morning on NPR; many of you may have already heard
>it.  It is a strong piece that sets up the call to action for dietary
>guidelines.  As some of you may know, not only is Allison Aubrey NPR's
>top science reporter with Dan Charles but also she is the mother of four
>kids who believes in whole, organic, pasture-raised milk, and a
>relationship we continue to build.  It will be interesting to see what
>other pick up the Swedish study gets.  Three of their sources were also
>referenced in our WSU study=8Broads leading in the right direction.  We
>also offered up Chuck and Don Davis as sources on this segment, and Greg
>Miller is perhaps someone to connect with going forward.  Excerpts from
>George's interview with her yesterday did not make it in, but we were
>really pleased to be one of her first calls as sources.
